27/06/2004
LISBON, Portugal -- Greece qualifies for the semi-finals of Euro 2004 after a 1-0 victory over France, described as "one of the biggest shocks in the history of the European Championships" on Friday (25 June). 
Greece is now plays the winner of Sunday's quarterfinal between the Czech Republic and Denmark. 
(AFP, MPA - 26/06/04; AP, Reuters, AFP - 25/06/04)
